(2944, '1234212892', 'Hi John, thanks for cotticnang Plugin Dynamo Support.Unfortunately there is no way to increase/decrease the check email time limit. It is set to every 15 minutes though and fires off through a WordPress cron job. But your hick up might be coming from the fact that WordPress cron jobs don''t work exactly like a regular server cron job. Every time an action happens on your site, someone lands on any page, you log in as admin, you browse admin pages your WordPress install fires off the cron, and scans through at what job''s are set to run at that time, if no jobs are set to run, nothing happens. If there are jobs it runs them.So that''s why there''s a little bit of give and take on the time. No action on the site = cron doesn''t fire to retrieve emails.You can however manually retrieve the emails by visiting settings > email settings this will force a check.Or you can edit the time limit yourself in the code, by editing line #427 Currently:  interval'' => 900, to a desired time you want (in seconds) 900/60 = 15 minutes.5 minutes would be 300If you change it this way, de-activate the Plugin and re-activate it and the new schedule time should be in the cron job for you. Just be sure to go back and re-edit the line should you ever update the Plugin.Thanks,Plugin Dynamo Support', 'Youssef', '2014-02-11 20:42:19', 0, 0, 0, NULL),
