('1234400578', 'Cocoa', '1234400578.jpg', '78', 'Cocoa - The seed of this South American tree (Theobroma Cacao) have been used for food since ancient times, the Aztecs of Central America called it food for the gods, believing it was of devine origin. This is also reflected in its scientific name, Theos = gods, broma = food. In Aztec community only those of importance were allowed to drink the bitter beverage made form pounded roasted cacao beans, maize and chilli pepper. Today major cocoa producers include Brazil, Ghana and Ivory Coast ', NULL, 361, '2009-02-12 00:44:34', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL),
