('1238970482', 'Monkey', '1238970482.jpg', '98', 'The monkeys are locally powerful symbols, an physical expressing of life growth and vigor in the communities. They symbolize the status of the community at a particular point in time, the future and any mishap or success that may come on their way. For instance, the â€˜Cryingâ€™ of the monkeys continuous symbolizes trouble coming into the community. Captions from www.greenshepherdghana.org/', NULL, 353, '2009-04-05 20:52:45', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 3, 1, 1, 0, NULL),
('1238970961', 'Duasidan Monkeys', '1238970961.jpg', '98', 'The new monkey sanctuary discovered at Duasidan in the Dormaa District of the Brong-Ahafo Region is over 120 years old and the sacred grove brings to two, the number of such sanctuaries in the region. The other one is at Buabeng-Fiema in the Nkoranza district.', 'FBALw-B-qmg', 561, '2009-04-05 20:52:45', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 7, 2, 1, 0, NULL),
('1239235792', 'Accommodation', '1239235792.jpg', '99', 'There is just one choice of accommodation in Mole National Park, but there are also local guesthouses in nearby areas. Restaurants in Mole National Park cater for tourists, as well as possibilities for both driving and walking safaris.', NULL, 322, '2009-04-09 00:06:18', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL),
