('1239236786', 'Xylophone', '1239236786.jpg', '99', 'The gyil, an ancient xylophone, is the national instrument of the Dagara and Lobi nations of Ghana, Burkina Faso and Ivory Coast. The instrument is made with 14 wooden keys of an African hardwood called liga attached to a wooden frame, below which hang calabash gourds. Spider web silk covers small holes in the gourds to produce a buzzing sound, and antelope sinew and leather are used for the fastenings. ', NULL, 298, '2009-04-09 00:06:18', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL),
('1239237007', 'Wardance', '1239237004.jpg', '99', 'Wardances: a different rhythm is used during the historic wardance. For this occasion men are dressed in a traditional smock with a colourful cap and holding bows and arrows with quivers as a symbol of bravery.(SWOPA: Sirigu women organisation of pottery and art). ', NULL, 390, '2009-04-09 00:06:18', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL),
('1239237137', 'Swopa', '1239237136.jpg', '99', 'The village is well known for its traditional architecture, pottery and wall designing. Since 1997, more than 150 women of Sirigu have formed an organization for pottery and art (SWOPA: Sirigu women organisation of pottery and art).', NULL, 433, '2009-04-09 00:06:18', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL);
