('1253461954', 'Lincoln University Football Squad of 1939 -1941', '1253461954.gif', '155', 'Sitting: 2nd from Left Dr. Ebenezer Ako Adjei Standing: 1st from left Dr. Kwame Nkrumah\r\n\r\nNkrumah arrived in New York  towards the end of October 1934 and began his studies in Economics and Sociology at the Lincoln University  . In 1939 he obtained his B.A. degree with major in Economics and Sociology, and in 1942 qualified as Bachelor of Theology. He proceeded to the University  of Pennsylvania  in Philadelphia  where he obtained an M.Sc. degree in Education and an M.A. in Philosophy. While at the University of Pennsylvania  , he helped to set up the African Studies section there. He also helped to organize African students in America  and Canada  into an African Students Association of America and Canada  . At the first congress of the Association, he was , elected its president. ', NULL, 482, '2009-09-20 15:42:27', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL),
