('5023af87db466', 'Waakye', '5023af87db4a8.jpg', '172', 'Waakye is a very popular Ghanaian food. It is often eaten as breakfast or launch, and sold by vendors on the streets of big and small cities alike in Ghana. The most basic form is made by boiling rice and beans together though variants include the addition of tomatoes, chillies, spices fish, prawns and assorted meats. This gentle prefers to eat his waakye from the big green leaf, says he''s unable to break tradition!', NULL, 250, '2012-08-09 12:33:24', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL),
('5023af87d3fa2', 'Bambara Beans and tatale', '5023af87d3fea.jpg', '172', 'The classic way to serve tatale is with boiled bambara beans (aboboe) as in the photo above, or bean stew. Tatale and aboboe is a wonderful, elegantly simple party snack, especially pleasant when washed down with cold glasses of beer. It is also hearty enough for nonvegetarians to adore', NULL, 254, '2012-08-09 12:33:21', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL);
