('5023af87d8fd9', 'Bambara Beans Seller', '5023af87d901b.jpg', '172', 'Somewhere in Adabraka, a woman fries Tatale ( pounded rip plantain). This is served with boiled Bambara beans. Most people hate to prepare this at home because of the confusing ingredients that go into it. But trust me it''s always worth the try, it''s delicious!!!', NULL, 239, '2012-08-09 12:33:23', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL),
('1272216708', 'Ave Maria Resort and Wellness Centre', '1272216708.jpg', '182', 'Ave Maria Holdings acquired the property and has upgraded and added many more facilities making the Resort an International Tourist Hotel, Conference Centre, Sport and Entertainment Venue, and Health Spa destination.\r\nThe resorts main emphasis is on Health Care and Fitness.\r\nThe dedicated and qualified Staff and Management are always willing to assist and be of service to the many Visitors and Guests.\r\nHealth is not a luxury\r\nHealth is the key to a Prosperous and Happy Life.', NULL, 376, '2010-04-25 17:19:19', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL),
('5023acf7e56e1', 'Food is ready!!!!!!', '5023acf7e5725.jpg', '174', 'You are done with the soaking of your gari and can start enjoying the sweet lunch.', NULL, 109, '2012-08-09 12:20:50', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL),
('5023acf7e25a8', 'Water time', '5023acf7e25ec.jpg', '174', 'Get a large bowl for soaking the gari. Make sure you have a lot cold water to soak the gari because cold water makes it taste good. With your gari in the bowl, pour cold water inside the bowl. You will see light substances showing up on the surface of the cold water. Pour those substances out of the bowl except getting rid of the gari. Afterward, make sure you pour some cold water inside the bowl to make sure the gari becomes all liquid. Don''t let the gari solidify or else you aren''t going to like your food. Gari is a similar to a nice cereal but it''s eaten as lunch. But one can also go straight to the point without washing to get the impurities out of the gari.', NULL, 102, '2012-08-09 12:20:49', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL),
('5023acf7dd831', 'Mixing it up', '5023acf7dd872.jpg', '174', 'Add sugar to the soaking and stir. Also, add a slight amount of salt to the gari. You cannot add too many tablespoons of sugar unless you aren''t afraid of diabetes. Pour your peanuts inside the bowl containing the soaking of gari, sugar and water. Stir promptly. Add evaporated milk to the soaking containing gari, sugar, slight amount of salt, water and peanuts. Your choice of milk will be fine but Carnation Milk makes this food tastes so sweet. Add enough milk to the gari soaking.', NULL, 105, '2012-08-09 12:20:47', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL),
('5023acf7d536c', 'Soaking Gari', '5023acf7d53ae.jpg', '174', 'Soaking gari is done by people from all over the world. Gari is a nice food eating by people from Nigeria, Ghana, parts of South America, North America, Asia and Europe. When soaking gari, there are things you should do in order to the gari taste good. A.J is a radio presenter at Hitz FM in Accra and enjoys Gari Soakings not because it''s easy to prepare but it tastes good to him. Here, he showed us how to prepare his favourite......... please read along you might pick some few points. Ingredients: (1)Gari (2) Evaporated milk or powdered milk (3)Sugar (4) A bit of salt (5) Peanuts and (6)Water', NULL, 433, '2012-08-09 12:20:45', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL),
('1272216742', 'Ave Maria Resort and Wellness Centre', '1272216742.jpg', '182', 'Ave Maria was built in the Early Fifties by Sir. W. Alcrow. The Resort is situated just meters from the Greenwich Meridian Rock.\r\nBefore the Queenâ€™s visit in 1962, the late President, Nkrumah ordered that a chalet and swimming pool should be built for the Queenâ€™s relaxation during her stay.\r\n\r\n\r\nAfter the Queenâ€™s visit the late President Nkrumah visited regularly and the flag was hoisted each time, indicating his presence.\r\nToday the chalet is a Guest room, called the Queenâ€™s Reading Room, guests get to overnight in this luxury and historical room, overlooking the pool.', NULL, 395, '2010-04-25 17:19:19', '968d139c8a89d54ac3f06fb287e91b249a644ed9', 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL),
