('1278333188', 'Tour Jeep', '1278333188.jpg', '202', 'You need to have your own car here. Walking is naturally prohibited in most areas of the park, and you wont get to see much sans a vehicle. They do have tours but you really do need your own vehicle to get around and to view the animals properly. There are many car hire companies in this area and their prices are competitive.', NULL, 268, '2010-07-05 12:33:08', 'admin', 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL),
('1278333385', 'Entrance Addo Elephant National Park', '1278333385.jpg', '202', 'Several historic sites can be found in the area which date back as far as 1829. The most well known site is the Drift House, the Inn used by most people crossing the Addo drift from the old Cape Colony into the Hinterland. ', '', 370, '2010-07-05 12:36:25', 'admin', 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL),
('1278333594', 'Addo Elephant National Park', '1278333594.jpg', '202', 'Come to Addo and see the famous Addo elephants as well as mile after mile of verdant citrus trees, bearing fruit all winter and scenting the air with their blossoms in springtime. ', '', 358, '2010-07-05 12:39:54', 'admin', 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL),
('1278334124', 'Addo Elephant National Park', '1278334124.jpg', '202', 'Addo Elephant National Park is situated 72km by road from Port Elizabeth. Established in 1931 to save 11 Elephants on the brink of extinction, and now home to more than 350 of them, 280 Cape Buffalo, black Rhino, a range of Antelope species, as well as the rare flightless dung Beetle, Addo Elephant Elephant Park is a perfect destination for the adventurous outdoor and nature lover. ', '', 494, '2010-07-05 12:48:44', 'admin', 11, 3, 1, 0, NULL),
('1278334055', 'Elephants', '1278334055.jpg', '202', 'The park, the third largest in South Africa, offers a wide range of game viewing and outdoor activities, which include horse-back and horse-riding, guided walking, hiking and 4x4 trails and a picnic area for day visitors. Nothing could be better if you are a bush lover. ', NULL, 412, '2010-07-05 12:47:35', 'admin', 5, 1, 1, 0, NULL),
