('1280081349', 'Dungeon', '1280081349.jpg', '205', 'The Dutch captured the fort in 1642 and traded slaves on a small scale until the abolition of the slave trade in 1807; the three dungeons â€“ for men, women and children â€“ only held about 25 slaves each, but by the time the Dutch sold the fort to the British the vultures had moved on to dead goats instead of dead slaves.', '', 354, '2010-07-25 18:09:09', 'admin', 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL),
