('1289111388', 'Jet Ski  Bojo Beach Resort ', '1289111388.jpg', '222', 'The white sand beach is very clean so it is not surprising that most patrons prefer to hang around there.To get here,drive pass MacCathy Hill and pass Weija junction, then you start looking out for the old police barrier just ahead, on your left-hand side of the barrier is the Apalku or Kokrobite junction.Keep driving and within 5 minutes, you will drive through the Apalku village, start looking out for the imposing yellow Bojo Beach sign post from here that directs you to the left, you toss onto the dusty road and within seconds you will say voila! To Bojo. There is so much car parking space and excellent security at the car park. ', '', 1103, '2010-11-07 06:29:48', 'admin', 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL),
