(881, '{"subject":"  posted a comment","message":{"comments":"Dear Mr. Rutter,I have sung for many years in a choir in Rio de Janeiro Brazil called Canto em Canto. Our cocudntor, Prof. Elza Lakszchevitz much cherished your work and I learned about it from her. I have many of your CDs conducting the Cambridge Singers, which are among my favorite music albums. I am a computational  scientist and I am now spending one year at Imperial College London, on sabbatical leave from my university in Rio, where I am a professor.  I would immensely enjoy being able to attend a concert with the Cambridge Singers, conducted by you, but I have not found any information regarding one such concert on the internet. I will be in London until September 2013 and would much appreciate any information regarding these concerts in the surrounding cities. I just attended the concert at the Royal Albert Hall yesterday, which was however with another choir.best wishes,Roseli"}}', '2014-02-11 09:38:55', '1'),
